<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="119" pageId="3" pageNumber="115" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1366,2040]" pageId="3" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1473,1499]" pageId="3" pageNumber="115">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Body medium size with pubescence. Head: frontal rostrum 2 times as wide as the 1st antennal joint (
<figureCitation box="[261,385,1510,1536]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[211,1375,188,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[211,1376,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Features of Mirigryllus nigrus sp. nov. A, male pronotum and forewing; B, female pronotum and forewing; C, male head in front view; D, male head in dorsal view; E, male hind tibiae and basitarsomere in dorsal view; F, male epiproct in dorsal view; G, ovipositor in lateral view; H, male genitalia in dorsal view; I, male genitalia in ventral view; J, male genitalia in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4443770" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4443770/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="115">Fig. 3C, D</figureCitation>
), vertex obviously flat, median ocellus flat, smaller than lateral ocelli and located lower than lateral ocelli (
<figureCitation box="[306,394,1546,1572]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[211,1375,188,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[211,1376,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Features of Mirigryllus nigrus sp. nov. A, male pronotum and forewing; B, female pronotum and forewing; C, male head in front view; D, male head in dorsal view; E, male hind tibiae and basitarsomere in dorsal view; F, male epiproct in dorsal view; G, ovipositor in lateral view; H, male genitalia in dorsal view; I, male genitalia in ventral view; J, male genitalia in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4443770" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4443770/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="115">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
), maxillary palpi with 3rd–5th joints long and 5th slightly widened (
<figureCitation box="[1165,1254,1546,1572]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[211,1375,188,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[211,1376,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Features of Mirigryllus nigrus sp. nov. A, male pronotum and forewing; B, female pronotum and forewing; C, male head in front view; D, male head in dorsal view; E, male hind tibiae and basitarsomere in dorsal view; F, male epiproct in dorsal view; G, ovipositor in lateral view; H, male genitalia in dorsal view; I, male genitalia in ventral view; J, male genitalia in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4443770" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4443770/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="115">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); thorax: pubescent, disc of pronotum as wide as head (
<figureCitation box="[614,706,1582,1608]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[211,1375,188,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[211,1376,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Features of Mirigryllus nigrus sp. nov. A, male pronotum and forewing; B, female pronotum and forewing; C, male head in front view; D, male head in dorsal view; E, male hind tibiae and basitarsomere in dorsal view; F, male epiproct in dorsal view; G, ovipositor in lateral view; H, male genitalia in dorsal view; I, male genitalia in ventral view; J, male genitalia in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4443770" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4443770/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="115">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
), anterior and posterior margin almost straight, rounded borders between disc and lateral lobes, tympanum on outside long and big, but very small on inner side, forewing not longer than 2 times of pronotum, 2 oblique veins curved, without crossvein between chord and mirror, mirror longitudinal elongated with 2 curved dividing vein, apical field short (
<figureCitation box="[801,892,1690,1716]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[211,1375,188,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[211,1376,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Features of Mirigryllus nigrus sp. nov. A, male pronotum and forewing; B, female pronotum and forewing; C, male head in front view; D, male head in dorsal view; E, male hind tibiae and basitarsomere in dorsal view; F, male epiproct in dorsal view; G, ovipositor in lateral view; H, male genitalia in dorsal view; I, male genitalia in ventral view; J, male genitalia in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4443770" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4443770/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="115">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Legs strong, hind femur little longer than hind tibiae, 5 pairs of dorsal spines alternated on hind tibiae, 5 pairs of spines on basitarsomere (
<figureCitation box="[1193,1280,1726,1752]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[211,1375,188,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[211,1376,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Features of Mirigryllus nigrus sp. nov. A, male pronotum and forewing; B, female pronotum and forewing; C, male head in front view; D, male head in dorsal view; E, male hind tibiae and basitarsomere in dorsal view; F, male epiproct in dorsal view; G, ovipositor in lateral view; H, male genitalia in dorsal view; I, male genitalia in ventral view; J, male genitalia in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4443770" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4443770/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="115">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
), epiproct triangle with apical part in arc-shape (
<figureCitation box="[561,647,1762,1788]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[211,1375,188,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[211,1376,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Features of Mirigryllus nigrus sp. nov. A, male pronotum and forewing; B, female pronotum and forewing; C, male head in front view; D, male head in dorsal view; E, male hind tibiae and basitarsomere in dorsal view; F, male epiproct in dorsal view; G, ovipositor in lateral view; H, male genitalia in dorsal view; I, male genitalia in ventral view; J, male genitalia in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4443770" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4443770/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="115">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
). Genitalia: epiphallus transverse with posterior epiphallic lobes long and thin, without a medial lobe at posterior, ectoparameron transparent with basal part wide, as long as posterior epiphallic lobes (
<figureCitation box="[343,480,1834,1860]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[211,1375,188,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[211,1376,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Features of Mirigryllus nigrus sp. nov. A, male pronotum and forewing; B, female pronotum and forewing; C, male head in front view; D, male head in dorsal view; E, male hind tibiae and basitarsomere in dorsal view; F, male epiproct in dorsal view; G, ovipositor in lateral view; H, male genitalia in dorsal view; I, male genitalia in ventral view; J, male genitalia in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4443770" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4443770/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="115">Fig. 3H, I, J</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1366,2040]" pageId="3" pageNumber="115">
Female. Similar to male including epiproct, veins on dorsal field of forewing not parallel, more or less crossed (
<figureCitation box="[160,247,1906,1932]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[211,1375,188,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[211,1376,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Features of Mirigryllus nigrus sp. nov. A, male pronotum and forewing; B, female pronotum and forewing; C, male head in front view; D, male head in dorsal view; E, male hind tibiae and basitarsomere in dorsal view; F, male epiproct in dorsal view; G, ovipositor in lateral view; H, male genitalia in dorsal view; I, male genitalia in ventral view; J, male genitalia in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4443770" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4443770/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="115">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
), ovipositor straight, without teeth on apical side (
<figureCitation box="[810,900,1906,1932]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[211,1375,188,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[211,1376,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Features of Mirigryllus nigrus sp. nov. A, male pronotum and forewing; B, female pronotum and forewing; C, male head in front view; D, male head in dorsal view; E, male hind tibiae and basitarsomere in dorsal view; F, male epiproct in dorsal view; G, ovipositor in lateral view; H, male genitalia in dorsal view; I, male genitalia in ventral view; J, male genitalia in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4443770" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4443770/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="115">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1366,2040]" pageId="3" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1941,1967]" pageId="3" pageNumber="115">Coloration.</emphasis>
Nearly black. One white transverse bar connecting lateral ocelli, but separated with median ocellus, maxillary palpi white, two vertical yellow line on occiput, indistinct yellow stripes behind eyes, tarsi and spurs brown (
<figureCitation box="[238,304,2014,2040]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[326,1262,181,1942]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[326,1262,181,1942]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mirigryllus nigrus sp. nov. in living condition.A, hatchling; B, junior instar; C, D, penultimate instar; E, F, ultimate instar; G, male (macropterous); H, female (macropterous); I, male (brachypterous); J, female (brachypterous)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4443768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4443768/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="115">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
G–J).
</paragraph>
